algorithm to find a local approximation for ground states of\ngapped local 1D Hamiltonians. When the Hamiltonian is translationally\ninvariant, we show that the ability to find $O(1)$-accurate local\napproximations to the ground state in $T(N)$ time implies the ability to\nestimate the ground state energy to $O(1)$ precision in $O(T(N)\\log(N))$ time.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Mar 2019 11:07:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 7 May 2019 06:29:24 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 19 Sep 2019 04:19:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-25"}
